        "description": "Granular reload scope used when failure.category = 'Router Reload'. Platform-conditional: 'Router' (full chassis) and 'RP' (route processor) apply to all three architectures (Fixed, Centralised, Distributed); 'MPA' and 'SC' apply only to Centralised platforms; 'LC' and 'FC' apply only to Distributed platforms.",
        "items": [
          { "name": "Router", "applies_to_architecture": ["Fixed", "Centralised", "Distributed"], "notes": "Full-chassis reload of the device. Applies to all platforms." },
          { "name": "RP",     "applies_to_architecture": ["Fixed", "Centralised", "Distributed"], "notes": "Route Processor reload (active or standby), including RP failover. Applies to all platforms; on Fixed devices it functionally reloads the single CPU/control-plane complex." },
